  "description": [
    "J peetzUtob BY ELUOTT J PIEZE CIVIL RIGHTS A LOCAL PROBLEMIKE Quite a few of the local Negro Republicans and other supporters of President Eisenhower express ed disappointment over the Pres idents remarks on the civil rights issue in his speech ait In ternational Airport Monday after noon Despite the fact that many prominent Negroes have seen fit to style Ike as an ultra liberal in the matter of the civil rights and despite the faat that New York Congressman Adam Clayton Powell openly stated that he was bolting the Democratic Party and throwing his support behind the President because he did not agree with the Democrats platform on civil rights President Eisenhower in plain words said I urged then meaning in 1952 as I urge now the handling of this question meaning the civil rights issue to the greatest possible ex tent on a local and state bfsis In other words the President talked like a State Righter who advocates the handling the civil rights and all other important issues affecting the welfare of the Negro in this country by the states rather than on a national level This as any informed per son will tell you is simply"
